Constantly refining the basics ⚽️
——————————————————————————————
I always stress to clients how important it is to get your touches in each day. Weather it’s juggling outside, dribbling the ball through the house or training ball mastery in the back yard. Spend more time with the ball and improve your relationship with the ball. Does the ball look like it’s running away from you when it comes to you or does it look like you and the ball are inseparable. Juggling, ball mastery, dribbling 1v1 and just going outside and striking the ball will all help when it comes improving on the basics and help with overall relationship with the ball. But it comes down to how bad you want it….twice a week at training isn’t enough. Do these drills daily, you have my page for reference and if your confused or need help with a drill ask for help. I am always here! Hope you enjoy! ⚽️

Passing ——-> Finishing 
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with Alex and Aaron. Focusing on passing, spacing, and off ball movement in first video and transitioning to finishing to end the session. Really enjoyed this session with these two, intensity was high and touches were intentional. Solid session in the end with a great workout ethic from these two…still room for improvement but we celebrate small victories along the way. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Passing + First touch 
————————————————————————————Here’s a look into my session with Alex and Emorie. Focusing on passing and moving our first touch away from pressure to receive and plays again. Great work ethic from these two as always. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

READ CAPTION ⬇️
———————————————————————————————
What’s going on guys, if you haven’t noticed I haven’t been posting as much as previously…In 2021 I started a new journey in Kansas as a Graduate Assistant Coach in pursuit of my Masters Degree. I did a short stint there before returning to Florida where I again began a new journey for myself. Upon returning in early 2022, I took a full time position in sports media while continuing my Masters Degree as well as continuing my brand and business CBW Training. This in return left me spread thin for a short time, and is the result of my lack of activity on this account. With that being said, I recently graduated with my Masters Degree in Sports Business and I am really looking forward to putting time and energy back into my brand and business for 2023.  This year I will be posting more informational content, drill break downs, tutorials, skill demonstrations and more content. Get ready for CBW Training to take off this year, super excited to take this journey with you all.

Skill Moves ⚽️
—————————————————————————————
Here’s 3 of my favorite skill combinations to do while running at defenders. I played outside midfielder during my playing career and one of my favorite moments during the game was go to 1v1 at a defender and put him on skates. Give these skill combinations a try and let me know how it goes. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Great session with professional soccer player @jtisch11 Getting ready for his upcoming indoor season. John plays for the @tbstrikers which is a professional indoor team here in the Tampa Bay Area. First of many session with JT looking forward to developing throughout the season. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

BALL MASTERY ⚽️ 
——————————————————————————————
Here’s 4 ball mastery drills that you can do at home on your own. Last week I posted a few skill move combinations and I got a lot of questions on how I developed these skills. The simple answer…SPEND MORE TIME WITH THE BALL and if you don’t know how, here’s a few  drills that can begin to point you in the right direction. Part of this page is to help educate the youth on how to get better on your own as well as showcasing drills that you can imitate for your own personal gain. Give these drills a try and let me know how it goes. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Finishing⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look inside my session with Aaron. Focusing on skill moves to goal with a clean finish. Still need some work on our shooting technique. Need to spend more time shooting ball outside of training to get more comfortable with the technique. Still a ways to go but we can appreciate the small victories. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Juggling Tutorial 🚨
——————————————————————————————
What’s going on guys, one thing that I always emphasize on in early in development is to learn to juggle. This is one of the foundations of the game and helps translate to good first touch, weight of touch, control out of the air and so many other basics of the game. Juggling is a great place to start if you are just starting out your soccer journey or haven’t developed that part of your game yet. Here’s 5 easy steps to help you learn how to juggle. Give it a try and let me know how it goes! Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Foot work / Ball work ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look inside my session with Alex and Aaron. Focusing on clean feet through hoops and cones, spacial awareness as we open up into space and a clean pass to connect. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Drill Progressions ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a drill progression I like to use at the beginning of a training to get the feet going. Focus is on clean feet, strong passes, and skill work.  My goal is for Aaron to be as comfortable on the ball as possible when receiving, passing, and playing because these are the fundamentals of the game. Slowly getting to where we want to but still need to sharpen up some other areas of his game. Long way to go but we keep pushing. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Juggling Drill ⚽️
———————————————————————————————
Here’s a juggling drill that I like to use for control and just general practice. Take four cones and make a square. Place them about  1 yard apart from each other. The point of this drill is to stay within the square while juggling for as long as possible and keeping the ball below your knees. Give this drill a try and let me know how it goes! Hope you enjoy! ⚽️

Ball Work ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with @datboyq_98 Getting ready for his upcoming UPSL Season with the @spfc_aztecs Quality session as always running the big man through a few technical drills. Focusing on first touch away from pressure with a skill move to create space and time, passing and receiving and clean feet through cones to finish. Hope you enjoy!

I always get a lot of questions on how to pick the ball up when clients are starting out there juggling journey. The truth is there is a bunch of different ways you can learn to pick the ball up, you just have to see what’s fits best for yourself. My personal favorite is number 2…I learned that when I was about 12 and haven’t looked back since. Give these picks ups a try and let me know how it goes, If you guys would like a tutorial of these let me know in the comments and I will be sure to stitch a video together for you guys. Hope you enjoy⚽️

Warm up ——> Finishing ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with Q. Starting with a technical warm up to get the blood flowing. Focusing on keeping it clean and crisp in our passes and volleys and finishing with a shooting drill. Quality session, Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Here’s a look inside my session with professional soccer player @jtisch11. This is how we began our session starting with some SAQ Work to help get a sweat going and our heart rate up and then adding in the ball for the technical aspect of the warm up. This is a typical look and format on how I will begin my sessions with a slight twist in focus depending on training session. Thanks for watching! Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Ball Mastery ⚽️
——————————————————————————————
Heres 3 ball mastery drills for you guys to try. Each drill is a build off one another finishing with drill#3 which is a combination of both drill#1 and drill#2. Start slow and find your rhythm with each drill before progressing on. Remember the goal is BALL MASTERY here…not to just go through the motions. I see this all to often…it’s not good enough to just do it…you must challenge yourself. Hold yourself accountable. Create small goals within your BIG goals to hold yourself to that standard.  The overall objective and end goal here is to do these with speed, control and purpose to give us confidence to perform these movements in game with ease. Hope you enjoy ⚽️🙏🏽

Passing & Receiving ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look inside my session with Aaron, Emorie and Alex. Focusing on a crisp lay off, passing a receiving , and a skill move to create space and get your pass off. Been really pushing this group as we approach the summer grind. Separation session is coming soon looking forward putting the work in with this group. Hope you enjoy ⚽️
Instagram ——> Reality

Here’s a look inside my sessions these past few weeks. Quality sessions from these 10 year old BALLERS!  Focusing on creating a solid footwork foundation, ball mastery, and passing to finish. I recently started working with a new group of talented young boys that I am looking forward to develop. One thing I love about this group is there drive and dedication for the game. Most sessions I have to drag them off the field because they don’t want to stop training. That’s a mindset you can’t teach…that comes from your heart, it comes from how bad you want it and I am looking forward to fueling that ambition. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

To all the clients, friends and family who continue to believe in what we do here at CBW Training…. THANK YOU! Your support is unmatched. It’s a blessing to be able to help guide the youth on their personal soccer journey. Looking forward to the future. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Passing + First Touch

“Mistakes are welcome”
———————————————————————————————
Of course our aim isn’t to make mistakes intentionally, but if we do make a mistake, especially in a training setting it’s important to stay mentally strong to overcome this obstacle. At the end of the day the game is a mental battle and we are human. Mistakes CAN happen in the game and my question to you is how will you respond? Will you hang your head, feel sorry for yourself and sulk in the moment? Or keep your head high, shake it off and fight to get it back.  Coaches will see two different players, and two different responses depending on how you respond. You must be mentally strong. The mental piece of the game is something I stress to my clients daily, because adversity in the game and adversity in life is inevitable.  Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Ball Work / Footwork
———————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with Andy focusing on skill, ball work and passing and receiving. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

“What are you doing when no one is watching?”
———————————————————————————————
I always tell my clients when you are not working outside the game..the next player is. It’s about getting in good habits early to help you later in your career. You don’t just become professional when you sign that contract…it’s a process of training and approaching the game  like a pro from a young age because at the top no one has to tell players to do extra work. It’s already apart of their game. Hope you enjoy.

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

Here’s a look into my session with Andy. Focusing quick feet, skill moves and dribbling  to start, before transitioning into focusing on a nice firm layoff, punching through our pass to the wall, spacial awareness and nice technical shot to finish.  Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

READ CAPTION 📖
———————————————————————————————
As a coach who was a past player I see this all to often. A player with great skill, but bad attitude. A player with great talent, but poor habits outside the field. A player with confidence and charisma but struggles with criticism from players and coach. Notice how none of the qualities players struggle with are skill, talent or on field related, but these all have a huge impact on weather a player will make it or not.  This is where the hard work comes in. It’s hard work…to stay focused when everyone else wants to hangout with friends. It’s hard work to mentally stay strong when coach is ripping into you for a mistake, it is hard work to stay positive and supportive when your on the bench and not playing, it’s hard work to analyze your weaknesses and go out and train on your own. It’s HARD WORK…but hard work is how you get to the top and It’s going to take more than JUST talent to stay there. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

Never let someone else’s doubt, kill your own dreams. Let them talk, YOU are the only person in control of your future. NEVER let anyone define you or tell who you are…it might not seem like you are getting anywhere but small progress is STILL progress ALWAYS keep pushing forward! Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

First touch + Passing

Here’s a look into my session with Justin. Focusing on moving our first touch away from pressure and into space and crisp passing and receiving. Quality session from Justin as always, looking forward to what the future holds for this young baller! Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

I think there is a misconception when it comes to training and what it takes to get better. Youth players think if you just show up to team training twice a week or three times, it will be the answer to all the weaknesses you have in the game. That through time you will just acquire the skills of a good touch, technical foundation and a dangerous shot, without actually focusing on mastering this part of your game. This is the farthest from the truth. It doesn’t just happen one day because you’re older, it doesn’t get easier. YOU have  to put the time in. If you see a player with great skill, technical foundation and good mindset… know that is the result of hours of training, hours of discipline, self improvement and motivation, hours of failing, trying again and repeating until mastery. It doesn’t just happen one day. YOU HAVE TO PUT THE WORK IN. Hope you enjoy

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

Ball Mastery + Finishing

Here’s a look into my session with Andy. Focusing on skill moves, dribbling and creativity on the ball with a clean finish to end it. Super sleeky from Andy in this drill. Love the disguise and deception on the skill moves. This was our last session before he went to Spain for a month for trials.  Looking forward to more sessions with this young baller! Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidentontheball

It’s important to get out of your comfort zone in order to grow and develop.  As a coach I’m always trying to create an environment that is challenging and puts pressure on players to reach levels they thought weren’t possible. It’s important for players to understand that in order to do that you have to be subject to discomfort and in that discomfort you must fight to get out to the other side.  This is how you grow. This is a endless cycle you will experience both in the game and and life and it’s about how you react to each situation. During my sessions I am constantly reiterating this saying, pushing clients to limits, keeping the standard high and setting the tone. I see players react one of two ways. Either they thrive from the high standard and rise to the challenge and value the session or they succumb to the pressure, high standards and challenge and don’t enjoy the training session. The point I’m trying to make is the environment is meant to be challenging.  You are supposed to be uncomfortable. It is not supposed to be easy and the sooner you understand that the closer you will get to development and growth in this game. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidentontheball

Juggling / First touch + Ball Mastery ⚽️💪🏽 
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with Andy. Focusing on our touch out of air and ball control during partner juggling then transitioning to ball mastery in the second video. This is actually a homework assignment I’ve given each of my youth clients to better help master the ball. Give this drill a try and let me know how it goes. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidentontheball

This is a statement I constantly reiterate during my training sessions. I think it’s important to push clients, but I also think they need to LEARN the proper technique, footwork and ball mastery before doing so in order to ensure they are pushed in the correct direction. Understand it is okay to walk, that is the foundation so that we are able to learn to run.  Vice versa, during this learning phase I have players walk through drills and ball mastery patterns to better understand the drill and the small details we want to emphasize to create a better bigger picture. This allows players to find their rhythm at a pace that works for them, to create the technical  foundation so that we are able to speed it up for overall mastery and control.  To often I see players struggle to learn a technique or skill move, but haven’t learned the proper progressions to reach the proper end result. To them I say “let’s learn to walk, before you run” I will give players the blue print if they have questions all day long but I can not learn it for you! That part is up to you! Slow it down, and find out what works for you. LEARN TO LEARN.  Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidentontheball

It’s easier said then done of course. Adversity is difficult to over come at times, but this is why the mental part of the game is so important. You must stay strong and understand it’s all apart of the process. Learn from your mistakes, grow, then move onto the next challenge to repeat again. Repeat this until you have mastered your game and then some. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtraining #confidentontheball

Passing and Receiving
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with Jad. Focusing on passing and receiving with a skill move to create space or evade pressure.  Really want to emphasize on proper passing technique here in terms of punching through the ball to create a nice firm pass. We don’t want hospital balls. From a receiving  standpoint, focusing on keeping our head on a swivel and getting our hips open to see both ways to receive with our front foot. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtraining #confidentontheball

Our purpose for training: We train to learn, we train to get better, we train to grow, we train to develop our weaknesses and we train to develop our mentality. Plain and simple, and our intensity should match that. If we are here to get better like stated above, giving anything but 100% effort and intensity is negating our purpose. If you are giving anything less than 100% at my training sessions you will here it from me, why? Because we are here to learn and grow and build good habits and that is the standard here. Growing up my coaches used to tell me to not be upset when your coach is getting into you, and pushing you/ critiquing you to do better. That’s what they are there for, and it shows belief in the player. Players should be upset when a coach stops critiquing you/ noticing you. Not saying this is the answer but again, you are meant to be pushed. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Fundamentals ⚽️
———————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with jerimah. Focusing on half volleys , volleys and first touch out of the air. Super important to make time for these basic movements in the game as this translates to being able to strike the ball out of the air, as well as having a good first touch out of the air so that we are able bring the ball down and play. Quality from my lil 10 year old baller! Still not where we want to be but we keep pushing!  Hope you enjoy ⚽️ 

#cbwtrainings #confidentontheball

Competition is great, it is what drives us. We should want to win and hate losing, but understand that with a loss comes a lesson. Which is what is so great about competition. Competitiveness is something I encourage everyday at my sessions and in between clients. One thing you will hear me say consistently is “who’s gonna win?” EVERY TIME I don’t care who you’re training against, I expect you to say yourself and believe it! At CBW Training we are here to compete and through competing against players and ourselves, can we push our selves to limits we never imagined. Set standards within yourself and create an expectation for greatness, each and everyday. Challenge yourself to be better than the last drill, last mistake,  last goal. Challenge yourself to be better than you were the day prior . That’s what competition within yourself looks like and a trait I encourage to my clients consistently. Embrace it, enjoy the highs of winning, and learn from the lows of losing. Hope you enjoy ⚽️
#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

1 Touch + 2 Touch ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with Connor, super clean and technical session  from big man. Focusing on a clean lay off and moving our first touch into space to play. Love the sound of the rhythm in the passing.  You  can literally hear and see the consistency of the technique which I always tell my players…..You should know when you’ve found your rhythm…one it should come natural and two you should be able to hear it. Hope you enjoy!
#cbwtrainings #confidentontheball

I firmly believe in 100% effort, focus and attention to detail at each of my sessions. We are here to create good and consistent habits that can be valuable to us in the game.  It’s the quality of our session and consistency over time that will help reiterate these attributes…attention to detail..work ethic …focus throughout the whole session, mental resilience etc. These are all factors that directly correlate to the game. To often I see kids show up to train and think just showing up is good enough….it is good for nothing if your training session is poor and you are going through the motions and not pushing yourself. The quality of your session should be as close to game speed, mentality, and hunger as you can get. Keep your training sessions short and sweet but high in intensity, education, and purpose. Understand that you practice how you play, so tune in, focus up, and give everything you got to every training session to improve the way you train and play in games. Get the most out of every training session! Quality > Quantity! Hope you enjoy ⚽️

Passing & receiving ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into my session with Josie Jocelyn and jerimiah. Focusing on passing and opening up and receiving with our front foot with a clean lay off. Proper fundamentals of the game. P.S they all did 10 burpees  for missing the last pass on each of those reps. In my opinion that is unacceptable with no pressure, we should not be missing 5 yard passes, if we can’t do it here with consistency with no pressure, how do we expect to do it in the game with pressure? Create a standard for your training sessions and demand it from your players. Hope you enjoy ⚽️
#cbwtrainings

To me discipline is one of the most important characteristics in development. It is so important to understand as a player that regardless of the situation you STILL need to show up and do the right things.  The game is not going to wait for everything to be perfect for you. SHOW UP when your tired, SHOW UP when it’s HOT out,  SHOW UP when it’s cold and raining, SHOW UP when you don’t want to, but still you SHOW UP and do the right things. That is discipline and over time the ones who consistently do the right things separate themselves from the ones who pick and choose when to show up and work hard. Hope you enjoy ⚽️

#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

Finishing 🚀

Ball and a Wall ⚽️ | PART 1
————————————————————————————
Here’s a series to help educate players on different ways you can train on your own. This series aims to help educate players on how to work on their shooting, passing/ first touch and ball mastery on their own or with a partner. 
Too often I hear the excuse that players don’t have the necessary equipment or a partner to train with to improve. This is just an excuse to not put the work in, or you haven’t been taught the proper way to train on your own. All you need is a BALL AND A WALL and some creativity. Here’s an example of how you can work on your shooting by yourself with or without a partner. Find wall/ bench  Or buy a rebounder for $50 bucks at DICKS and get out there and improve. It’s all about reps and doing the right things consistently.  Hope you enjoy ⚽️
#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball

Passing + First Touch ⚽️
————————————————————————————
Ball and a Wall | PART 2
————————————————————————————
Here’s a look into an individual session with myself, like stated before I wanted to bring to you guys a series of how players can train on their own for maximum benefit.  Here’s a look at how players can train passing and first touch on their own. I started off just getting the feet warmed up with 1 touch passing and transitioned to two touches. My focus for two touches was to focus on a good first touch out from under our body  to set me up for my next pass. Really just trying to find consistency within the movement and create rhythm.  Lastly focusing on moving our first touch across our body and away from pressure! Focus on punching through that ball and over hitting your pass to demand a good touch from yourself! NO HOSPITAL BALLS! Keep the ball on the carpet. Really love this routine give it a try and let me know how it goes. Hope you enjoy ⚽️
#cbwtrainings #confidenceontheball
